  "name": "EIRS Leadership Model Framework",
  "summary": "**Conversation Overview**\n\nThe user requested help organizing content about strengths-based leadership into an Excel table format. They provided detailed information about the EIRS model (Executing, Influencing, Relationship Building, Strategic Adaptation), which appears to be a modified version of a leadership framework where \"Strategic Thinking\" was renamed to \"Strategic Adaptation.\" Each of the four categories contained specific leadership strengths, with some elements highlighted in bold (자기성찰, 엄정한 인사, 인재확보 열의, 지속성장 관심, 지속 학습) indicating they were likely additions to the original model. Claude created an interactive HTML table that visually resembled an Excel spreadsheet, complete with professional styling, clear categorization of the four leadership domains, and highlighted emphasis on the bolded elements from the original content. The solution included a CSV download function to allow the user to export the data for use in actual Excel software, and added contextual notes explaining the model changes and highlighting the newly added strength elements.",
  "created_at": "2025-08-27T00:42:18.713443Z",
  "updated_at": "2025-08-27T00:42:44.651296Z",
